  "text": "The above intuition suggests that when T has large singular values, its low-rank approximation T k is not perturbed much by E, and thus, low-rank approximations ofT are good reconstructions of T . A series of theorems by Achlioptas and McSherry [CITATION_1] and Kerenidis and Prakash [CITATION_2] formalizes this intuition. For brevity, we only describe a simplified form of the last theorem in this series, which is the version they (and we) use for analysis. It states that, under appropriate circumstances, it's enough to computeT σ ,η for appropriate σ and η. Then with probability at least 1 − exp(−19(log n) 4 ),",
